cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.AR, cs.SE, cs.NA

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper compares the performance of two frameworks for GPU programming, which is a topic related to parallel computing. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the conversion of a CUDA kernel to an OpenCL kernel, which involves modifications to the programming language. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is another possible category as the paper focuses on GPU programming, which is a topic related to hardware architecture. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper measures and compares end-to-end application execution times for both CUDA and OpenCL, which is related to software engineering practices. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper uses complex, near-identical kernels from a Quantum Monte Carlo application, which is a topic related to numerical analysis.
